[[<]]



,,{{//Due to the nature of EE-00059, classification as a proper SCP is unnecessary.[[footnote]]{{As of 04/24/2020, EE-00059 and all related documents are to be associated with SCP-001 as a primer for recently-declassified information.}}[[/footnote]] Knowledge of the existence of EE-00059 is credited as non-anomalous due in part by successful disinformation campaigns; therefore, no containment measures are required at this point. Any information regarding transmissions or activity arising from EE-00059's vicinity is to be confirmed as legitimate, then handled by agents stationed in various relevant positions worldwide, including but not limited to observatories, places of academia, and media outlets such as television studios and radio stations. At this time, all data concerning the true nature of the event is considered purged from public knowledge.//}},,



**Event Description:**  Extranormal Event 00059 was observed on June 14th, 2006, in a region of space roughly 1.6 billion light years from Earth,[[footnote]]Therefore indicating its initial source to be ~1.6 billion years in the past.[[/footnote]] located in the constellation Indus. It was detected via the Neil Gehrels //Swift// Observatory telescope system as a prolonged gamma ray burst designated [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GRB_060614 GRB 060614]. 



EE-00059-1 is an emergent Class-E "Momentary Lapse of Reason" Wormhole (S-CSMWAUC2T)[[footnote]]Spacial, Cycling Stability, Stationary, Manifested, Wide-Area, Uncertain, Conditional Two-Way, Transient. See: //[/forum/t-5174970/nothing-like-a-little-unnecessary-science-headcanon A Discourse on the Unification of Technological Canon, Vis-à-vis the Classification of Extradimensional Portals (i.e. Wormholes)]// and other [[[scp-3989|similar case files]]] for more information.[[/footnote]] that was observed for 102.0 seconds, during which it exhibited atypical behavior that contradicted all known theoretical and applied models of space-time folds.



[[include <a href="http://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/component:coltop">:scp-wiki:component:coltop</a>

| show= ◇ OPTIONAL SPECIFICATIONS AND ELABORATION

| hide= ◈ 

]]

During the event, EE-00059-1 was observed to behave in a manner that first resembled traditional [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wormhole#:~:text=A%20wormhole%20(or%20Einstein%E2%80%93Rosen,of%20the%20Einstein%20field%20equations. Einstein–Rosen wormholes], emitting unidentified matter and light, while otherwise resisting the inbound flow of normal matter and fatal to organic life due to topological decoherence.[[footnote]]Although topologically sound along their outer bounds, typical wormholes are not simply connected (n = 1) surfaces and thus possess ultra-compressed multidimensional topologies such as [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Calabi%E2%80%93Yau_manifold Calabi–Yau manifolds] at their center.[[/footnote]] Despite this, the region possessed a luminance several magnitudes greater than the predicted calculations implied, to an intensity only suggested to occur in [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/White_hole white holes], which have never been observed. 



Upon closer analysis, EE-00059-1 appeared to be exerting no effect on the surrounding space, evidence that implied the anomaly had little or no gravitational field. This is more consistent with [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ellis_drainhole Ellis drainholes], which are fully-transferable non-flat three dimensional regions of simply connected space-time folds.[[footnote]] 

[[math]]

{\displaystyle {\mathbf {R} }_{\mu \nu }-\textstyle {\frac {1}{2}}{\mathbf {R} }\,g_{\mu \nu }=-2\,\left(\phi _{,\mu }\phi _{,\nu }-\textstyle {\frac {1}{2}}\phi ^{,\kappa }\phi _{,\kappa }\,g_{\mu \nu }\right)\,.}

[[/math]]



[[/footnote]] These paradoxical behaviors cannot co-exist at once, as each feature has physical consequence that manipulates the region's own scalar field into a state that, by definition, cannot support the initial conditions of the others.

[[include <a href="http://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/component:colend">:scp-wiki:component:colend</a>]]





EE-00059-2 is a series of low-frequency transmissions that originated from the direction of EE-00059, during which EE-00059-1 was observed. All transmissions were in an unknown language with phonetic structure bearing similarities to Sumerian and Mapudungun,[[footnote]]A language spoken by some indigenous populations found in Southern Chile and Argentina.[[/footnote]] however, said language also contained unique dialects consisting of a complex creole of other, unknown lexicons, as well as an unfamiliar syntactical structure. 



Congnitohazardous glyphs embedded within the broadcast appeared to cause increased contextual/conceptual understanding of the meanings of the messages without need for direct translation. Combined with the atypical quality and range for transmissions to have originated from that distance, anomalous broadcasting equipment is suspected to have been used to send the messages (See **EE-00059-2 Transcript Logs** for more information). 



